# planning-verify-live-state-before-assuming-work-remains — History

## v1.3.0 (2026-06-19)

**Changed by:** SECOND /learn pass for GitHub issue #177 (Odysseus meta-repo, "GitHub rulesets in 'evaluate' mode not enforcing"). The first plan (v1.2.0) got a NOGO for being static-only; this re-plan resolved every NOGO finding by querying LIVE state with `gh api` instead of inferring from static config files.
**Verification:** verified-local for the core branch-migration workflow; the issue #177 ruleset FINDINGS are now verified-against-live (`gh api .../rulesets` was run this session). The #177 implementation PLAN itself remains proposed (not executed/merged).

### What changed

- **Promoted the #177 worked-example subsection from UNVERIFIED → live-verified.** Replaced the
  "static-only, never queried" warning with the confirmed live findings: live ruleset id 15556483 is
  already `active` (the OPPOSITE of the issue's "evaluate" claim); exactly 8 bare-name contexts +
  `integration_id: 15368`; `forbid-suppressions` is the deliberately non-required 9th job; the org
  endpoint 404s on the FREE plan. Documented the re-planned minimal additive scope (deletes nothing).
- **Added 4 new Detailed Steps (11–14):** deployed state may be the OPPOSITE of the issue's claim
  (idempotent re-apply can DOWNGRADE enforcement); one live query collapses several unverified
  assumptions; reconcile doc-vs-doc number disputes against the deployed system; prefer additive
  changes and never remove an operational rollback/safety path as a side effect.
- **Added 3 new Failed Attempts rows:** (a) trusting the issue's stated state without querying live →
  would have downgraded enforcement; (b) static-only first plan → NOGO on 5 MAJOR findings;
  (c) bundling deletions/refactor into a one-line fix → rollback regression. Annotated the prior
  `integration_id` row as confirmed by the live ruleset.
- **Updated the description, When-to-Use, and Overview Verification row** to cover drift-opposite,
  one-query-resolves-many, and doc-vs-doc-against-deployed-state; bumped version 1.2.0 → 1.3.0;
  date stays 2026-06-19.

### Why

v1.2.0 captured the #177 first-pass plan as a set of UNVERIFIED static-only assumptions and got a
NOGO. The re-plan ran the one `gh api .../rulesets` query the reviewer flagged as missing, which
collapsed five separate NOGO findings at once and revealed the live ruleset was already `active` —
so the real fix is drift-closure (and a naive idempotent re-apply of the stale on-disk `evaluate`
file would have DOWNGRADED live enforcement). The durable learning is a planning-discipline one:
verify live external state before planning a config fix, especially when the deployed state can be
the inverse of the issue's claim. These findings extend the same search surface this skill already
owns, so they are amended in rather than split out.

### Previous version (v1.2.0) snapshot

```yaml
name: planning-verify-live-state-before-assuming-work-remains
category: tooling
date: 2026-06-19
version: "1.2.0"
verification: verified-local
```

v1.2.0 framing (now superseded): the #177 ruleset subsection was titled "UNVERIFIED, static-only
plan" with a warning that the live org/repo ruleset state was NEVER queried; it listed the bare-vs-
prefixed context format, the 9-vs-8 count, the org-endpoint availability, and `integration_id: 15368`
as assumptions taken on faith. v1.3.0 confirms each against the live ruleset (id 15556483). The
v1.2.0 Failed-Attempts rows tagged `(#177, UNVERIFIED)` are retained for the historical record; the
re-plan rows tagged `(#177, re-plan)` carry the resolutions.

